<div style="font-family: Calibri; text-align: justify; font-size:
14.54px;">Dear Sir / Ma&rsquo;am,<br /><br /> Greetings!<br /><br /> We are
glad to inform you regarding our forthcoming programme on <b>Finance for
Non Finance Executive</b>. The 4.5 days program for Managerial roles are
increasingly getting cross functional and interdependent. Financial impact
of any managerial decision‐making is all pervasive, with the need for a
non‐finance manager to assess the impact of his functional decisions made
on the top line (Sales) and the bottom line (Profits), becoming
indispensable<br /><br /> <b>Key Topics :</b>
<ul style="margin-top: 0px;">
<li>Understanding Corporate Financial Statements</li>
<li>Understanding &amp; determining Cost flows in an organisation</li>
<li>Using Cost information for decision making</li>
<li>Analyzing &amp; Interpreting Corporate Financial Statements</li>
<li>Introduction to Corporate finance</li>
<li>Overview of Indian Financial Markets</li>
<li>Working capital Management</li>
<li>Capital Budgeting</li>
<li>Financial Risk Management</li>
</ul>
<b><u>Programme Directors : -</u></b><br /> Prof. Manju Jaiswall is an
Associate Professor in the Finance and Control group at IIM Calcutta. She
has done her M.Phil in Commerce from Calcutta University and doctorate in
Management from IIM Bangalore.<br /><br /> Prof. Purusottam Sen has a B.S.
from Birla Institute of Technology &amp; Sciences, Pilani (India), an MBA
(specialization in Financial Management) and a PhD (Fellow of IIM Calcutta)
from Indian Institute of Management Calcutta (India).<br /><br />
<b><u>Participant Profile:</u></b> The programme would be immensely useful
for functional heads, team leaders, supervisors desirous of understanding
financial statements and managing costs, irrespective of their domain area
of work.<br /><br /> <b><u>Programme Duration and Venue:</u></b> The
programme will be conducted from June 08 - 12, 2019 at IIM &ndash; Calcutta
campus.<br /><br /> Check in: June 07, 2019 (6:00 pm onwards)<br /> Check
out: June 12, 2019 (2:00 pm)<br /><br /> <b><u>How to apply:</u></b>
